reviewText: Loved the glimpse into behind the scenes...TOFOG definitely rocks the house...sounds like they need to be experienced live to be appreciated fully...although trying to get to all the different levels of the DVD was quite a challenge, I'm sure ole Russell is laughing....but the frustration was well worth it...after viewing this can't wait to see them live!
Title: 30 Odd Foot of Grunts - Texas

reviewText: I bought this because I thought it was going to just be a concert. It was alot of talking and showing when and where they go, it was very boring to me.
Title: 30 Odd Foot of Grunts - Texas

reviewText: Before tossing this one in the trash, know that there is an easier way to access the extras.  Delightful and funny documentary of a very decent bar band.  Crowe's voice isn't Pavorotti, but it is passable, especially on songs meant to rock.  Not cracked up with his balladeering, but there is an interesting rap type track of a little song called "Nowhere".Now to those harder than hell to get to levels.  DVDs like Texas have titles and chapters.  Most DVD player remotes come with a display button.  Hit the display button and navigate the titles starting with 1 then 2 and so forth through 20.  It is a very easy way to get around this DVD without going through all those inane instructions.  I really don't know who's idea the levels were, but they must have been in some sort of dream state.
summary: So the Hidden Levels Drive You NUTS...........
Title: 30 Odd Foot of Grunts - Texas

reviewText: I only knew about TOFOG several yrs ago and when I decided to search out any possible DVD concert performances, I thought it was a bit of a stretched that there might even be one made. To my surprise, I search it out here on Amazon.com with Fingers X'd, and there it is! I thoroughly enjoyed it, even the the language was rather rough at times. Definitely a great ADD to my growing DVD Concert collection, now up to about 32. 31 are bands/artists and the other is George Carlin.
Title: 30 Odd Foot of Grunts - Texas

reviewText: I enjoyed this dvd immensely.  It gives alot of background and day to day info of the band and their lives.  I really enjoyed it.
